<a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=93762'><h3>View taxon page for Chloropyron</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#YL1'">1.</a><a name="YL1."> </a> Fertile stamens 4; inner bracts entire or slightly notched <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93763">.....&nbsp;C. maritimum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#YL2'">2.</a><a name="YL2."> </a> Inner bracts generally entire; seeds 25&ndash;40, 1&ndash;1.5 mm; inland <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93764">.....&nbsp;subsp. canescens</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#YL2.">2'</a><a name="YL2'"> </a> Inner bracts slightly notched; seeds 10&ndash;20, 2&ndash;3 mm; generally coastal

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#YL3'">3.</a><a name="YL3."> </a> Stem generally much-branched, distal branches generally > central spike; seeds &plusmn; 2 mm; s Central Coast, South Coast <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93765">.....&nbsp;subsp. maritimum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#YL3.">3'</a><a name="YL3'"> </a> Stem 0&ndash;few-branched, branches &lt;= central spike; seeds 2&ndash;3 mm; North Coast, n Central Coast <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93766">.....&nbsp;subsp. palustre</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#YL1.">1'</a><a name="YL1'"> </a> Fertile stamens 2, staminodes 2; inner bracts 3&ndash;7-lobed

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#YL4'">4.</a><a name="YL4."> </a> Leaf 1&ndash;2 mm wide; inner bracts 3-lobed; style puberulent <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93769">.....&nbsp;C. tecopense</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#YL4.">4'</a><a name="YL4'"> </a> Leaf 3&ndash;8 mm wide; inner bracts 3&ndash;7-lobed; style glabrous

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#YL5'">5.</a><a name="YL5."> </a> Plant soft-hairy to becoming glabrous, longest hairs &lt; 1 mm; seed coat deeply netted, wavy-crested <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93768">.....&nbsp;C. palmatum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#YL5.">5'</a><a name="YL5'"> </a> Plant, especially inflorescence, glandular-puberulent and stiff-long-nonglandular-hairy, longest hairs > 1 mm; seed coat deeply netted, not wavy-crested <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93767">.....&nbsp;C. molle</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#YL6'">6.</a><a name="YL6."> </a> Stem much-branched from near base; inflorescence generally 2&ndash;6 cm; corolla pouch and tube sparsely tomentose; seed 1&ndash;1.5 mm; Great Central Valley <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93770">.....&nbsp;subsp. hispidum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#YL6.">6'</a><a name="YL6'"> </a> Stem generally few-branched from middle; inflorescence 5&ndash;15 cm; corolla pouch and tube densely tomentose; seed 2&ndash;3 mm; n Central Coast, deltaic Great Central Valley <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93771">.....&nbsp;subsp. molle</a></blockquote><P>
